reviewText: A very funny and rare piece if you like silent films,one of the greats. These go back a ways and that's what I like about them. It gets away from the ordenary.

Strictly for hardcore fans of silent comedy, this one is well worth your USD6 and ninety minutes of your time.. in fact there's evidently a second volume , which should give some idea of how well this one was received. Alpha has released other volumes Forgotten Funnymen - Al St. John: Fatty and Mabel's Simple Life (1915) / Waiter's Ball (1916) / Stupid But Brave (1924) / Bridge Wives (1932) Turpin Time: Ben Turpin Comedy Classics (Broke In China / A Harem Knight / Why Ben Bolted / Yukon Jake) (Silent) Snub Pollard Showtime: Vitamin V Or Me / Big Idea / Join The Circus / Courtship of Miles Sandwich / An Auto Nut Leon Errol Comedy Collection as well, some designated "Forgotten Funnymen," others not.
